c with query&#8221; option by default only for the first Product Catalog instance, disable for 2nd and next ones <a href=\"https://github.com/woocommerce/woocommerce/pull/44577\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">#44577</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/woocommerce/woocommerce/trunk/changelog.txt\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">See changelog for all versions</a>.</p>\n\";s:11:\"screenshots\";s:1035:\"<ol><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/woocommerce/assets/screenshot-1.jpg?rev=2366418\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/woocommerce/assets/screenshot-1.jpg?rev=2366418\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/woocommerce/assets/screenshot-2.jpg?rev=2366418\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/woocommerce/assets/screenshot-2.jpg?rev=2366418\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/woocommerce/assets/screenshot-3.jpg?rev=2366418\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/woocommerce/assets/screenshot-3.jpg?rev=2366418\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/woocommerce/assets/screenshot-4.jpg?rev=2366418\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/woocommerce/assets/screenshot-4.jpg?rev=2366418\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/woocommerce/assets/screenshot-5.jpg?rev=2366418\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/woocommerce/assets/screenshot-5.jpg?rev=2366418\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/woocommerce/assets/screenshot-6.jpg?rev=2366418\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/woocommerce/assets/screenshot-6.jpg?rev=2366418\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ol>\";s:7:\"reviews\";s:16798:\"<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">always has issues customer support sucks</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jamiea1988/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4f0551d2a4a5407f2ae1b6ba057bde0c?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4f0551d2a4a5407f2ae1b6ba057bde0c?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jamiea1988/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">jamiea1988</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">April 12, 2024</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">I loved how the layout and everything that came with the plugin but I have had an issue every single time a wholesale client has tried to checkout and customer service is no help what so ever so ive had to hire developers to fix issues. Im switching over to another plugin because im losing money and time trying to fix issues</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">INSOPORTABLES UPDATE</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/pexcreative/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/afad8306a316bc935145d24fcf3db785?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/afad8306a316bc935145d24fcf3db785?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/pexcreative/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Ezequiel Del Vacchio <small>(pexcreative)</small></a> on <span class=\"review-date\">April 11, 2024</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">Todos los días actualizaciones y encima para PEOR!<br />Años actualizando y actualizando y ARRUINAN el SEO de lo mal que funcionan.<br />Ya no tiene sentido tener una tienda totalmente inestable. Para que actualizan tanto si cada vez funciona peor. SIMPLEMENTE WORDPRESS y WOOCOMMERCE se van de mi server.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Update 8.7.0 Customers Unable to Checkout</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jacs2023/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/51195608dc2e865d82d2de07eef8ada2?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/51195608dc2e865d82d2de07eef8ada2?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jacs2023/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">jacs2023</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">March 30, 2024</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">Since the new update - and for the past month none of my customer are able to checkout. Constant messages of invalid or missing payment details. Because I don\'t have a paid extension Woo Support is refusing to assist or even entertain that there is an issue.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">If I cannot resole this tomorrow I\'m changing to Shopify.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">woocommerce is a pain since 8.4</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jmsynth/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/676c21a6aaa34e897e9f157e0a9375ba?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/676c21a6aaa34e897e9f157e0a9375ba?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jmsynth/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">jmsynth</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">March 28, 2024</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">Since 8.4 it triggers too many false positive on modsecurity, crash any website under plesk/debian11/Comodo ruleset... adds unwanted cookies, calls external apis, force new functionalities, too bulky for what the average shop owner needs... well... now i\'m afraid of updating this plugin... are you even testing your plugin before put it in production ? and last but not least extensions are overpriced. Cant wait for an alternative, in the meantime i will suggest my client to move to another platform.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Nothig swown after update 8.7.0</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/rubenmora/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e66a3272414dfacbd40726741cab9ffb?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e66a3272414dfacbd40726741cab9ffb?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/rubenmora/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Ruben <small>(rubenmora)</small></a> on <span class=\"review-date\">March 27, 2024</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">I tried in dif ways but it is impossible. After the installation of 8.7.0 I cant see the web and I cant access to the administrator of wordpress. <br />My php 7.4 and using Divi. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Error in WooCommerce after change in XAMPP</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"3 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"3\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/blaugrana/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/7b4968cfdb49cb61c2907f669f67989b?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/7b4968cfdb49cb61c2907f669f67989b?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/blaugrana/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Мария Рангелова <small>(blaugrana)</small></a> on <span class=\"review-date\">April 10, 2024</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">Hello :) Until a month ago, I had a working WooCommerce. But now it crashes my whole site. I\'m developing locally on Xampp when I try to access the site dashboard and it gives me a network related error. I did a brand new installation of WordPress and gradually added the plugins. And the moment I installed WooCommerce everything exploded - it kicked me out again and gave me the error I mentioned.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Problem with checkout and Multi Currency for WooCommerce plugin</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/uni12/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f1b75caeb666b9e18ca6354d00391d83?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f1b75caeb666b9e18ca6354d00391d83?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/uni12/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">uni12</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">March 26, 2024</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">Hello, I updated the latest version of Woocomerce, 1st it does not save the short description or the downloadable files.<br />I can write the description correctly and put the pdf file to download but when I click update it is deleted.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">2nd I use the latest version of the Multi Currency for WooCommerce plugin establishing USD as the main currency and $ as the s